// Semantic direction:
// timeseries stores sequences of metric samples indexed by timestamp and label set.
// metric_labels are key-value pairs that distinguish instances (host, region, service).
// ts_chunk is a compressed block of samples covering a time range, the unit of storage and compaction.
// ts_range_query returns all samples for a metric within a time range.
// ts_instant_query returns the most recent sample at or before a given timestamp.
// tumbling_window divides time into non-overlapping fixed-size intervals.
// sliding_window moves forward by window_slide, so windows overlap by (window_size - window_slide).
// session_window groups events that occur within window_gap of each other into one session.
// window_assign maps each event to the window(s) it belongs to.
// wf_rate computes the per-second rate of change for a monotonically increasing counter.
// wf_increase returns the total increase of a counter over the window duration.
// wf_percentile computes the p-th percentile value over the window.
// downsample reduces resolution by aggregating multiple samples into one per downsample_interval.
// fn_mean averages all samples in the interval; fn_last_ds keeps the most recent.
// interpolation fills gaps in sparse time series: linear between known points, step holds the last value.
// fill_previous repeats the last known value forward until a new sample arrives.
// ewma (Exponentially Weighted Moving Average) weights recent samples more heavily via ewma_alpha.
// z_score measures how many standard deviations a sample is from the moving_avg.
// anomaly_detect uses z_score or iqr_bounds to flag samples that exceed anomaly_threshold.
// rollup_rule automatically downsamples high-resolution data to lower-resolution rollup_dst.
// stale_marker indicates a metric has stopped reporting; used to avoid stale data in queries.
// promql_expr is a PromQL query string; flux_query is the InfluxDB Flux language.

// Primitive flow:
// ingest: sample(value, ts, labels) -> ts_store.ts_write -> chunk append
// range query: ts_range_query(metric, start, end, labels) -> chunk scan -> samples
// tumbling window: assign_tumbling(event_ts, window_size) -> window_key (start, end)
//   collect events per key -> wf_sum/count/avg at window_end -> emit result
// session window: event -> extend session if gap < window_gap else close + open new
// anomaly: moving_avg(window=1h) + ewma(alpha=0.1) -> residual -> z_score -> flag if > threshold
// rollup: background job, every rollup_interval -> downsample(raw, fn_mean) -> write to rollup_dst
// retention: ts_compaction: chunks older than ts_retention -> drop or archive

// This defines time-series storage, tumbling/sliding/session windows,
// aggregation functions, downsampling, anomaly detection, and query languages.
